rComments: I wouldn't recommend this prof for any course, he is very rude and condescending. The course itself has presentation, 2 papers and a final exam. The final exam is very difficult, you are required to memorize 3 essays and write about it on the exam.
Unique prof who takes some time to get used to. once you do you'll realize hes a pretty good professor

Prof has a big mouth and he always brags about himself, his lectures are boring and he was never on track with course material. One question comes to mind during his lecture is "I spent my tuition on some ego-centric person to brag about himself during lecture?" Dont expect your assignments to be back on time, however, he marks easy.

I have had Dr. MacLellan in first year, he was not that awesome. But in this third year class I took with him, he has been amazing at helping students out, staying approachable, etc. You need to actually talk to him to learn how crazy knowledgeable he is and to really benefit from that knowledge.

I personally found his lectures dry especially since he didn't use a mic. Majority of the slides on the powerpoint come directly from the textbook itself, although don't focus too much on the terms - it's barely any help on the exams. The extra things he put on the powerpoint are usually important.

He just rambles on about data and he doesn't teach the specifics but will bring specific detail questions in the exams. Overall he is not a good teacher but he is a good researcher. I had to study hard to get a decent mark.

He was fairly one of the more enjoyable profs I had in the semester. He may have rambled during his lectures, however, he was generous when it came to how he structured the midterm final exam. Attend the lectures and you should be good to go!

he talks about very useless things in the lectures and then on the exams he puts things that are not found in the textbook, but from outside sources that he does not articulate clearly for us to find. the TAs are okay but the assignment are very silly
